#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:3 47f7d5c527594475881d209d0e8424f8
msgid "Passwordless root access in qubes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:6 c4002bb3ac7f4827be3a053e97bebb8b
msgid ""
"The background to passswordless root access is summarised in this "
"statement, that used to be found at ``/etc/sudoers.d/qubes`` in each "
"qube:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:58 0a2a0cfc66d946159cac9bb08a821d85
msgid ""
"The core of this statement continues to reflect the views of the Qubes "
"developers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:60 d769205792384b4faaf24515cbf7233b
msgid ""
"Passwordless root is provided by the ``qubes-core-agent-passwordless-"
"root`` package."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:62 2066844acfad43f9bbd188818cc23769
msgid "Details of the implementation are :doc:`here </developer/system/vm-sudo>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:64 883187f32f8041fca7afc0c6d3388e9b
msgid ""
":doc:`Minimal templates </user/templates/minimal-templates>`, which are "
"intended for use by advanced users, do not have this package installed by"
" default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:67 9a6fb6d0b4fd41bf9f95b1f1dc9f0160
msgid "Replacing passwordless root access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:69 c14a3d8ada69414cae4d6d6a7a4e6477
msgid ""
"Some users may wish to modify their system by enabling user/root "
"isolation in qubes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:71 ad90833253114ffaaeaa1d623468c360
msgid ""
"We do not support this in any packages, but users are free to remove the "
"qubes-core-agent-passwordless-root package if they wish, using standard "
"packaging tools."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:74 590fef081b9e441bb52ce15bc535f91e
msgid ""
"Root access can then be gained from dom0 by (e.g) ``qvm-run -u root QUBE "
"qubes-run-terminal``, or ``qvm-console-dispvm QUBE``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:77 ebf3e7a3d8d24f9d984af7f9305bcdd8
msgid "Replacing passwordless root access with Dom0 user prompt"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:79 1ea41969fea94fd49c1b861f2956fd9d
msgid ""
"An alternative approach is to enable user/root isolation by using a dom0 "
"generated prompt."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:81 cd4fb202e8404647af0edea44bd6812c
msgid ""
"A list of steps to do so is provided in the `Qubes community guide, "
"Replacing passwordless root with a dom0 prompt <https://forum.qubes-"
"os.org/t/replacing-passwordless-root-with-a-dom0-prompt/19074>`__ "
"**without any guarantee of safety, accuracy, or completeness. Proceed at "
"your own risk. Do not rely on this for extra security.**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:85 3a995a5083d74bedab2d262d77c7527a
msgid "Dom0 passwordless root access"
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:87 e4fb0274bae547aea2f905f9c9b32202
msgid "There is also passwordless user->root access in dom0."
msgstr ""

#: ../../user/security-in-qubes/vm-sudo.rst:89 edf10421115249c2a2b88cdf976fb909
msgid ""
"As stated in the comment in ``/etc/sudoers.d/qubes`` there is really no "
"point in user/root isolation in dom0, because all user data (and the "
"whole Qubes management interface) is already accessible to the user, so "
"there is nothing more to be gained from the dom0 root account."
msgstr ""

